# SAMPLE-OUTDIR — template for build-pdfs output redirection
#
# To use: rename (or copy) this file to OUTDIR or .OUTDIR inside a song
# directory. build-pdfs then redirects the PDFs it builds for songs in that
# directory according to the contents below.
#
# Format:
#   - One line is a destination directory path; a leading ~ is expanded. PDFs
#     are written there instead of next to the .song source.
#   - Optionally add a line reading BOTH (or COPY) to build locally AND copy the
#     PDFs to that directory, keeping both. Without it the build goes straight
#     to the directory, with no local copy.
#   - Optionally add a line reading SUBDIR to fan each song's PDFs into a
#     per-song subdirectory of the destination, <dest>/<base>, instead of flat.
#     <base> is the song's base filename with any -CAPO / --chords wrapper-or-
#     view suffix stripped, so Song.song, Song-CAPO.song and the --chords/
#     --lyrics view twins all land in <dest>/Song/. The subdirectory name must
#     match the song's base filename; build-pdfs creates it if it doesn't exist.
#     SUBDIR is orthogonal to BOTH (use both to keep a local copy as well).
#   - Blank lines and #-comment lines (like these) are ignored, and the path and
#     keyword(s) may appear in any order.
#   - If the path is missing or is not a directory, build-pdfs warns and falls
#     back to the usual local output.
#
# OUTDIR / .OUTDIR are meant to be git-ignored, so each machine or checkout can
# point somewhere different (keep SAMPLE-OUTDIR tracked as the reference).
#
# Edit the path below and uncomment it (drop the leading "# ") to activate;
# uncomment BOTH as well if you also want a local copy kept.

# BOTH
# ~/Dropbox/songsheets
